WHEREAS, following his retirement, he moved from Illinois to Florida and served his
community by volunteering at the Cape Coral Hospital for twenty-one years in the transport
department, moving patients throughout the hospital in wheelchairs or gurneys until COVID
forced an end to the volunteer program at the hospital in 2020; and
WHEREAS, Charles Bottens was joined in holy matrimony with Elaine Zaloudek in June
1955, and they were blessed with two daughters, Cynthia and Laura; the couple shared sixty-
five years of marriage until her passing in 2020; and
WHEREAS, as Mr. Bottens celebrates his 100th birthday, he remains a source of
inspiration to his family and community, embodying the values of perseverance, service, and
devotion that define his generation; and
WHEREAS, we wish to grasp this golden opportunity to specially recognize one of
Tennessee's most outstanding citizens on this very special occasion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Charles Edward Bottens
on the celebration of his 100th birthday and extend to him our best wishes for many happy
returns of the day.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
